# Unistyles Usage Guidelines

Use react-native-unistyles for all styling in the app. Follow these patterns:

## Setup and Theme

- Define theme in a central theme file with colors, spacing, typography
- Use createUnistylesTheme for type-safe theme creation
- Support light and dark themes

## Creating Styles

- Use StyleSheet.create() with theme and runtime parameters
- Access theme values for all design tokens
- Keep style definitions close to components
- Use the styles object directly without hooks

## Best Practices

- Never use inline styles - always use unistyles
- Use theme values for all colors, spacing, and typography
- Create reusable style utilities for common patterns
- Use variants for conditional styling
- Leverage runtime values when needed
- Keep style definitions close to components

## Common Patterns

- Use theme.spacing for consistent spacing
- Use theme.colors for all color values
- Use theme.fontSizes for typography
- Create semantic color names (primary, secondary, danger, etc.)
- Use theme.borderRadius for consistent rounded corners
